1.  Checkout jEdit build-support into the directory above this directory:

  svn co https://jedit.svn.sourceforge.net/svnroot/jedit/build-support/trunk build-support

2.  Edit the build.properties file to match your jEdit installation
3.  Run 'ant' to build
4.  Run 'ant dist' to install into your jEdit

----
Installing Ant For Windows

1.  Download Ant
2.  Unzip the file into a directory
3.  Set the environment variable $ANT_HOME to point to the directory
4.  Add the directory $ANT_HOME\bin to the Path environment variable

----

Install the ARM toolchain (arm-none-eabi-gcc)

https://launchpad.net/gcc-arm-embedded

1.  Test the compiler by running 'arm-none-eabi-gcc' from the command line.

